Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Chrysaor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0247.24.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Trimming suggests provenance)
